          "text": [
            "Q: what is prompt caching in claude code?\n",
            "\n",
            "A: Prompt caching in Claude Code is a mechanism that makes the system faster and more cost-efficient by reusing previously processed prompts instead of reprocessing the entire history on every turn. It automatically manages which parts of the conversation are cached and only performs new work for what has changed. This helps optimize performance and reduce costs associated with API usage. However, certain actions can invalidate the cache, leading to slower and more expensive responses while the cache is rebuilt [1][3].\n",
            "\n",
            "--- Sources used ---\n",
            "  [1] How Claude Code uses prompt caching  —  https://code.claude.com/docs/en/prompt-caching\n",
            "  [2] Model configuration  —  https://code.claude.com/docs/en/model-config\n",
            "  [3] How Claude Code uses prompt caching  —  https://code.claude.com/docs/en/prompt-caching\n",
            "  [4] Model configuration  —  https://code.claude.com/docs/en/model-config\n",
            "  [5] Modifying system prompts  —  https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/modifying-system-prompts\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
